What is shuffling in Apache Spark, and when does it happen?Apache Spark 中的混洗是什么？它何时发生？

When does an Apache Spark cluster perform the shuffle operation?Apache Spark 集群何时执行 shuffle 操作？
Bartosz Mikulski 20 May 2022 – 7 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2022 年 5 月 20 日 – 阅读 7 分钟

If you work with Apache Spark, shuffling is probably the leading cause of your problems.如果您使用 Apache Spark，则混洗可能是导致问题的主要原因。

Have you ever seen a computation failure because the data doesn’t fit on a single worker node? Do you wonder why Apache Spark couldn’t use multiple nodes in such cases?您是否遇到过由于数据不适合单个工作节点而导致计算失败的情况？您是否想知道为什么 Apache Spark 在这种情况下不能使用多个节点？

Does your cluster spend most of the computing time sending data between worker nodes, and all your queries are painfully slow?您的集群是否花费大部分计算时间在工作节点之间发送数据，并且您的所有查询都非常慢？

Every time something bad happens in Spark, blaming shuffling is a good guess, even if you don’t know what happens. What is shuffling, though? And why do we need it?每当 Spark 中发生不好的事情时，即使您不知道发生了什么，也可以将其归咎于洗牌。那么什么是洗牌呢？为什么我们需要它？

What is shuffling?什么是洗牌？

Apache Spark processes queries by distributing data over multiple nodes and calculating the values separately on every node. However, occasionally, the nodes need to exchange the data. After all, that’s the purpose of Spark - processing data that doesn’t fit on a single machine.Apache Spark 通过将数据分布在多个节点上并在每个节点上单独计算值来处理查询。然而，偶尔，节点需要交换数据。毕竟，这就是 Spark 的目的——处理单台机器无法容纳的数据。

Shuffling is the process of exchanging data between partitions. As a result, data rows can move between worker nodes when their source partition and the target partition reside on a different machine.混洗是分区之间交换数据的过程。因此，当源分区和目标分区驻留在不同的计算机上时，数据行可以在工作节点之间移动。

Spark doesn’t move data between nodes randomly. Shuffling is a time-consuming operation, so it happens only when there is no other option.Spark 不会在节点之间随机移动数据。洗牌是一项耗时的操作，因此只有在没有其他选择的情况下才会发生。

When do we need shuffling?什么时候我们需要洗牌？

Spark nodes read chunks of the data (data partitions), but they don’t send the data between each other unless they need to. When do they do it? When you explicitly request data repartitioning (using the repartition functions), when you join DataFrames or group data by a column value.Spark 节点读取数据块（数据分区），但除非需要，否则它们不会在彼此之间发送数据。他们什么时候做？当您显式请求数据重新分区（使用重新分区函数）时、当您连接 DataFrame 或按列值对数据进行分组时。

In the case of repartitioning, we shouldn’t be surprised. We requested repartitioning, so Spark does what we wanted. What about joining and grouping?在重新分区的情况下，我们不应该感到惊讶。我们请求重新分区，因此 Spark 执行我们想要的操作。加入和分组怎么样？

Imagine you have to pack 150 birthday presents. Chill out ;) You aren’t doing it alone. Two other people work with you. You’re preparing lousy gifts: a pair of socks and a scented candle, but the recipient could pick the scent! Who wouldn’t like to choose what crappy gift they get? ;)想象一下，您必须打包 150 份生日礼物。冷静下来；）你不是一个人在做这件事。另外还有两个人和你一起工作。你正在准备糟糕的礼物：一双袜子和一支香薰蜡烛，但收件人可以选择气味！谁不想选择自己收到的蹩脚礼物呢？ ;)

Packing the socks is relatively easy. You split the gift bags among the team, and every person puts 50 pairs of socks into the bags. That’s like being a Spark node without the shuffle operation. You do your part of the work and don’t care about the other workers.包装袜子相对容易。你将礼品袋分给团队，每人将 50 双袜子放入袋子中。这就像一个没有 shuffle 操作的 Spark 节点。你只做你的部分工作，不关心其他工人。

However, the job gets tougher as soon as your actions depend on the data you see. While packing the candles, you have to see who gets the present, find the person’s favorite scent on the list, pick the candle from the correct box (or bring the package from the storage room), and put the candle in the right bag.然而，一旦您的行动取决于您看到的数据，工作就会变得更加困难。在包装蜡烛时，你必须看看谁收到了礼物，在清单上找到这个人最喜欢的气味，从正确的盒子里挑选蜡烛（或从储藏室拿来包裹），然后将蜡烛放入正确的袋子里。

But we can make it easier! Before we even start, everyone groups their bags by the desired candle scent. You end up with nine piles of bags (3 piles per person). Now, every one of you picks one scent. You got lavender. You have to gather all bags of people who want a lavender candle and bring them to your part of the room. Your colleagues do the same. As a result, every worker has the data they need.但我们可以让它变得更容易！在我们开始之前，每个人都根据想要的蜡烛香味对他们的行李进行分组。您最终会得到九堆袋子（每人 3 堆）。现在，你们每个人都选择一种气味。你有薰衣草。你必须聚集所有想要薰衣草蜡烛的人，并将他们带到你所在的房间。你的同事也这样做。因此，每个工人都拥有他们需要的数据。

You have just completed the first shuffle operation.您刚刚完成了第一个随机播放操作。

Now, you can go to the storage room. In the storage room, you do the second part of the shuffling. After all, you need only the boxes with lavender candles. You search for the right boxes and bring them to the packing room. Now, you can put the candles into the bags you prepared earlier. Congratulations. You have joined two “datasets.” ;)现在，你可以去储藏室了。在储藏室里，你进行洗牌的第二部分。毕竟，您只需要装有薰衣草蜡烛的盒子。您寻找合适的盒子并将它们带到包装室。现在，您可以将蜡烛放入之前准备的袋子中。恭喜。您已经加入了两个“数据集”。 ;)

Spark isn’t as clever as a human, so it needs a mathematical operation to determine which data belongs to a worker. When we join the data in Spark, it needs to put the data in both DataFrames in buckets. Those buckets are calculated by hashing the partitioning key (the column(s) we use for joining) and splitting the data into a predefined number of buckets.Spark 不像人类那么聪明，因此它需要数学运算来确定哪些数据属于工作人员。当我们在Spark中加入数据时，它需要将两个DataFrame中的数据放入桶中。这些存储桶是通过散列分区键（我们用于连接的列）并将数据拆分为预定义数量的存储桶来计算的。

We can control the number of buckets using the spark.sql.shuffle.partitions parameter.我们可以使用spark.sql.shuffle.partitions参数来控制bucket的数量。

The same hashing and partitioning happen in both datasets we join. The corresponding partitions from both datasets are transferred to the same worker node. The goal is to have the data locally on the same worker before we start joining the values. We did the same when we sorted the gift bags and brought the right boxes from the storage room in our present packing example.我们加入的两个数据集中都会发生相同的哈希和分区。两个数据集中的相应分区都传输到同一个工作节点。目标是在开始连接值之前将数据本地存储在同一工作人员上。在我们当前的包装示例中，当我们对礼品袋进行分类并从储藏室取出正确的盒子时，我们也做了同样的事情。

Spark partitions the data also when we run a grouping operation and calculate an aggregate. This time we have only one dataset, but we still need the data that belongs to a single group on a single worker node. Otherwise, we couldn’t calculate the aggregations.当我们运行分组操作并计算聚合时，Spark 也会对数据进行分区。这次我们只有一个数据集，但我们仍然需要属于单个工作节点上的单个组的数据。否则，我们无法计算聚合。

Of course, some aggregations, like calculating the number of elements in a group or a sum of the parts, don’t require moving data to a single node. If we calculate the sum on every node separately and then move the results to a single node, we can calculate the final sum.当然，某些聚合（例如计算组中元素的数量或各部分的总和）不需要将数据移动到单个节点。如果我们分别计算每个节点上的总和，然后将结果移动到单个节点，我们就可以计算出最终的总和。

However, query optimization by calculating partial aggregations isn’t always possible. Therefore, in general, grouping requires the shuffle operation.然而，通过计算部分聚合来优化查询并不总是可行的。因此，一般情况下，分组需要进行shuffle操作。

What’s the most common problem with shuffling in Apache Spark?Apache Spark 中的洗牌最常见的问题是什么？

What if one worker node receives more data than any other worker? You will have to wait for that worker to finish processing while others do nothing.如果一个工作节点接收到的数据比任何其他工作节点多怎么办？您必须等待该工作人员完成处理，而其他工作人员则不执行任何操作。

While packing birthday presents, the other two people could help you if it turned out that 120 people want a lavender candle and you are the one doing most of the work. It’s natural for humans, but Apache Spark node workers can’t coordinate and share parts of a single partition. The unlucky worker node has to finish the task on its own while the others wait.在打包生日礼物时，如果有 120 个人想要一支薰衣草蜡烛，而你是大部分工作的人，那么另外两个人可以帮助你。这对人类来说很自然，但 Apache Spark 节点工作人员无法协调和共享单个分区的各个部分。不幸的工作节点必须自己完成任务，而其他节点则等待。

What’s even worse, the worker may fail, and the cluster will need to repeat a part of the computation. You can avoid such problems by enabling speculative execution - use the spark.speculation parameter. With this feature enabled, the idle workers calculate a copy of long-running tasks, and the cluster uses the results produced by the worker who finished sooner.更糟糕的是，worker 可能会失败，集群需要重复一部分计算。您可以通过启用推测执行来避免此类问题 - 使用spark.speculation参数。启用此功能后，空闲工作线程会计算长时间运行的任务的副本，并且集群会使用较早完成的工作线程生成的结果。

When does one worker receive more data than others?什么时候一名工作人员会比其他工作人员收到更多数据？

It happens when one value dominates the partitioning key (for example, the null). All rows with the same partitioning key value must be processed by the same worker node (in the case of partitioning). So if we have 70% of null values in the partitioning key, one node will get at least 70% of the rows.当一个值主导分区键（例如 null）时，就会发生这种情况。具有相同分区键值的所有行必须由同一工作节点处理（在分区的情况下）。因此，如果分区键中有 70% 的空值，则一个节点将获得至少 70% 的行。

When this happens, we have two options.当这种情况发生时，我们有两个选择。

First, we can isolate the dominating value by filtering it out from the DataFrame. After filtering, we can calculate the aggregate using the remaining rows. After that, we can calculate the aggregate of the filtered out value separately. It may help because we should have more resources available while calculating the aggregate of a smaller dataset.首先，我们可以通过从 DataFrame 中过滤出主导值来隔离它。过滤后，我们可以使用剩余的行来计算聚合。之后，我们可以单独计算过滤掉的值的聚合。这可能会有所帮助，因为我们在计算较小数据集的聚合时应该有更多可用资源。

We can also redistribute the values of the filtered out dataset using a different partitioning key, calculate a partial aggregate, and then combine them to get the final result.我们还可以使用不同的分区键重新分配过滤后的数据集的值，计算部分聚合，然后将它们组合起来以获得最终结果。

The second solution is to create a surrogate partitioning key by combining multiple columns or generating an artificial partitioning value. Such a key should help us uniformly distribute the work across all worker nodes.第二种解决方案是通过组合多个列或生成人工分区值来创建代理分区键。这样的密钥应该可以帮助我们在所有工作节点上均匀地分配工作。

Of course, sometimes, we can’t split the work into partial aggregates or use surrogate keys because we would get an invalid aggregate value. We need to deploy a Spark cluster with more powerful nodes for such situations.当然，有时，我们不能将工作拆分为部分聚合或使用代理键，因为我们会得到无效的聚合值。针对这种情况，我们需要部署节点更强大的Spark集群。

Can’t we do better?我们不能做得更好吗？

The simplicity of the partitioning algorithm causes all of the problems.分区算法的简单性导致了所有问题。

We split the data once before calculations. Every worker gets an entire partition (sometimes multiple partitions), and they don’t share the data until everyone finishes their task.我们在计算之前将数据分割一次。每个工作人员都会获得整个分区（有时是多个分区），并且在每个人都完成任务之前他们不会共享数据。

Wouldn’t it be better if nodes coordinated the work and helped the worker who got stuck with the largest partition? I don’t think so. In such a case, we would complain about an inefficient coordination algorithm. The process would resemble pushing papers between corporate departments. Can you imagine doing it efficiently?如果节点协调工作并帮助陷入最大分区的工作人员不是更好吗？我不这么认为。在这种情况下，我们会抱怨协调算法效率低下。这个过程类似于在公司部门之间推送文件。你能想象高效地做到这一点吗？

Theory of constraints in data engineering数据工程中的约束理论

Are you busy, but nothing ever gets done? Perhaps, theory of constraints will help you你是否很忙，却什么事情也做不成？也许，约束理论会帮助你
Bartosz Mikulski 25 Jun 2021 – 5 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2021 年 6 月 25 日 – 阅读 5 分钟

I must admit I almost gave up on writing this article. The more I read about the theory of constraints, the more it looked like a concept invented by consultants. Yet, at some point, I realized the ugly truth. Ignoring the theory of constraints was the root cause of many problems in my software projects.我必须承认我几乎放弃了写这篇文章。我对约束理论了解得越多，它就越像是顾问发明的概念。然而，在某个时刻，我意识到了丑陋的事实。忽视约束理论是我的软件项目中出现许多问题的根本原因。

What is the theory of constraints?什么是约束理论？

The theory is shockingly simple: In every system, there is only one factor limiting the entire system’s throughput.该理论非常简单：在每个系统中，只有一个因素限制整个系统的吞吐量。

A simple statement, yet we can derive quite complex consequences from it:这是一个简单的陈述，但我们可以从中得出相当复杂的结果：

  • only one top constraint exists仅存在一个顶级约束

It may be obvious to everyone who understands the meaning of the word “top.” But, on the other hand, some people have twenty top priorities at once, so maybe the definition of “top” not self-evident.对于每个理解“顶部”一词含义的人来说，这可能是显而易见的。但是，另一方面，有些人同时有二十个最重要的优先事项，所以也许“最重要”的定义不是不言而喻的。

  • improvements to other constraints don’t matter until we deal with the top constraint在我们处理最高约束之前，对其他约束的改进并不重要

If one factor limits the entire system’s output, ignoring the top factor won’t increase the overall performance. We can feel productive and look busy working very hard on fixing unimportant problems. Yet, we shouldn’t try improving everything else before we address the root issue.如果一个因素限制了整个系统的输出，忽略最重要的因素不会提高整体性能。我们会感到富有成效，并且看起来很忙，非常努力地解决不重要的问题。然而，在解决根本问题之前，我们不应该尝试改善其他一切。

  • we need metrics我们需要指标

We need them not only to find the most significant bottleneck. We’ll use them to verify whether our work made any difference.我们需要它们不仅是为了找到最重要的瓶颈。我们将用它们来验证我们的工作是否有所作为。

What do we do with the top constraint?我们如何处理顶部约束？

How do we deal with bottlenecks? The proponents of the theory of constraints suggest a five-step process:我们如何应对瓶颈？约束理论的支持者提出了一个五步过程：

  1. Identify - first must find the top constraint. If you think that many factors are top constraints, you are wrong. It means you failed to identify the real constraint.识别——首先必须找到顶部约束。如果您认为许多因素是首要限制因素，那您就错了。这意味着你未能识别真正的约束。
  2. Exploit - do everything you can in the current situation to improve the entire system without dealing with the root cause. The goal here is to check whether a simple tweak is good enough. Perhaps, after a minor alteration, the process becomes much faster. But does it mean we solved the problem? No, but maybe something else becomes the new top bottleneck.利用——在当前情况下尽一切努力改进整个系统，而不处理根本原因。这里的目标是检查简单的调整是否足够好。也许，经过微小的改变，这个过程会变得更快。但这是否意味着我们解决了问题呢？不，但也许其他东西会成为新的最大瓶颈。
  3. Subordinate - exploit other parts of the system to reduce the bottleneck. Look for workarounds and easy wins.从属——利用系统的其他部分来减少瓶颈。寻找解决方法并轻松获胜。
  4. Elevate - deal with the constraint directly. If every other attempt failed, removing the bottleneck is the only solution.提升 - 直接处理约束。如果所有其他尝试都失败了，消除瓶颈是唯一的解决方案。
  5. Repeat - there is only one top constraint, but there is always at least one constraint. After you fix the most significant issue, you can move to the next problem. Find the new top constraint, and repeat the process.重复 - 只有一个顶级约束，但始终至少有一个约束。解决最重要的问题后，您可以转到下一个问题。找到新的顶部约束，然后重复该过程。

The human constraint人类的约束

The theory of constraints helps you identify and solve the problem. However, it does not tell us what to do when a person is the top constraint in an organization. It happens for various reasons: gatekeeping, being a toxic person, laziness, lack of required skills combined with an unwillingness to obtain them, etc.约束理论可以帮助您识别和解决问题。然而，它并没有告诉我们当一个人是组织中的最高约束时该怎么做。发生这种情况的原因有多种：看门人、有毒的人、懒惰、缺乏所需技能且不愿意获得这些技能等等。

A “human constraint” complicates the process. People are the only constraints that retaliate. If you identify them as the bottleneck, they’ll fight back. No surprises here. If someone told you were the largest problem, you would fight too.“人为限制”使这个过程变得复杂。人是报复的唯一限制。如果你认为他们是瓶颈，他们就会反击。这里没有什么惊喜。如果有人告诉你这是最大的问题，你也会反抗。

The trick here is to blame the process. Of course, we’ll not address the root cause - the person. Although, we can build a process around the person. The process safeguards everyone else or forces the person to change their behavior. It is not a nice solution either. The person will, most likely, feel attacked anyway. There are no “nice” solutions to problems caused by someone’s personality.这里的技巧是归咎于过程。当然，我们不会解决根本原因——人。尽管如此，我们可以围绕人建立一个流程。这个过程可以保护其他人或迫使人们改变他们的行为。这也不是一个好的解决方案。无论如何，这个人很可能会感到受到攻击。对于由某人的个性引起的问题，没有“好的”解决方案。

Theory of constraints in data engineering数据工程中的约束理论

What are the most significant constraints in data engineering projects? From my observation, it’s usually the thing causing a long cycle time. Does the team look busy but nothing ever gets done? Do they seem overworked but underachieving?数据工程项目中最重要的限制是什么？根据我的观察，这通常是导致周期时间长的原因。团队是否看起来很忙，但什么事情都没有完成？他们是否看起来工作过度但成绩不佳？

I have seen two reasons for such situations.我发现这种情况有两个原因。

Tons of bugs and maintenance work大量的错误和维护工作

The team spends most of the time fixing the problems. Or rather “fixing” the issues because they are correcting the output data. The team doesn’t have time to address the underlying problem: too many bugs, no time to fix them properly.团队大部分时间都花在解决问题上。或者更确切地说“修复”问题，因为它们正在纠正输出数据。团队没有时间解决根本问题：错误太多，没有时间正确修复它们。

The solution here is to introduce proper testing gradually. In data engineering projects, we must test both the code and the input data. I also suggest testing the output data to make sure we don’t propagate a bug downstream. If your project is falling apart, it is even better to start with the output data verification. It gives you instant benefits.这里的解决方案是逐步引入适当的测试。在数据工程项目中，我们必须测试代码和输入数据。我还建议测试输出数据，以确保我们不会向下游传播错误。如果您的项目正在崩溃，最好从输出数据验证开始。它给你带来立竿见影的好处。

The team is working very hard, but nothing ever gets delivered团队非常努力，但什么也没有交付

Usually, the root cause is ill-understood perfectionism. Quite often, it happens to data scientists. They want to build the perfect model. So they gather more data, train larger models, tune them for weeks, but nothing ends up in production.通常，根本原因是不被理解的完美主义。这种情况经常发生在数据科学家身上。他们想要建立完美的模型。因此，他们收集了更多数据，训练了更大的模型，调整了数周，但最终没有投入生产。

What is the value of software that doesn’t run in production? Zero? Too much. Such software has negative value. You spent money building it, and it doesn’t make money.不在生产环境中运行的软件有什么价值？零？太多了。此类软件具有负面价值。你花了钱建造它，但它不赚钱。

The solution to the perfectionism problem is user story mapping. It is a technique of splitting huge features into incremental steps. Each step, when deployed, delivers value to the user.完美主义问题的解决方案是用户故事映射。这是一种将巨大的特征分解为增量步骤的技术。部署后的每个步骤都会为用户带来价值。

Usually, you don’t need the complete solution right away. You can deploy an MVP and gradually extend it. If people can’t use a half-done feature, I suggest adding feature toggles. You can still deploy the code in production, show the progress to a selected group of users, and don’t affect everyone else’s workflow.通常，您不需要立即获得完整的解决方案。您可以部署 MVP 并逐步扩展它。如果人们无法使用半成品功能，我建议添加功能切换。您仍然可以在生产中部署代码，向选定的用户组显示进度，并且不会影响其他人的工作流程。

Data engineering数据工程 Apache Kafka阿帕奇·卡夫卡

How does a Kafka Cluster work?卡夫卡集群如何工作？

What is the difference between a leader and a replica broker? What is the cluster controller? How is the controller elected?领导者和副本经纪人有什么区别？什么是集群控制器？控制者是如何选举的？
Bartosz Mikulski 18 May 2020 – 6 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2020 年 5 月 18 日 – 阅读 6 分钟

In this article, I am going to explain the building blocks of a Kafka Cluster. I am NOT going to write about consumers, producers, connectors, and streams. Instead of that, I will focus on servers and internal processes.在本文中，我将解释 Kafka 集群的构建块。我不会写关于消费者、生产者、连接器和流的内容。相反，我将重点关注服务器和内部流程。

However, before we begin all of that, we have to start with the concept of topics.然而，在我们开始这一切之前，我们必须从主题的概念开始。

Partitioning分区

Every topic has one or many partitions. It is possible to parallelize reading from a topic by using a consumer group that consists of multiple consumer applications. Each of those applications reads from one partition of the topic.每个主题都有一个或多个分区。通过使用由多个消费者应用程序组成的消费者组，可以并行读取主题。这些应用程序中的每一个都从主题的一个分区读取。

On the other hand, when we send a message, we may add a partitioning key to the record. Kafka producer is going to calculate the hash of the partitioning key and use that value to assign the record to a partition.另一方面，当我们发送消息时，我们可能会向记录添加分区键。 Kafka 生产者将计算分区键的哈希值并使用该值将记录分配给分区。

Interestingly, Kafka no longer uses round-robin partitioning as the default partitioning method. Since Kafka 2.4, producers use the “sticky” partitioning strategy (org.apache.kafka.clients.producer.internals.DefaultPartitioner). Right now, Kafka picks a partition randomly and sends the whole batch to that one partition. After that, it randomly picks another partition that will receive the next batch.有趣的是，Kafka 不再使用循环分区作为默认分区方法。从 Kafka 2.4 开始，生产者使用“粘性”分区策略（org.apache.kafka.clients. Producer.internals.DefaultPartitioner）。现在，Kafka 随机选择一个分区并将整批数据发送到该分区。之后，它随机选择另一个分区来接收下一批。

Kafka Brokers卡夫卡经纪人

Kafka cluster consists of a set of broker servers (three or more) that are identified by a unique numeric id. Every broker can have one of two roles in the cluster. It can be either a leader broker or a follower broker (there is also a special “controller” role, that we will discuss later).Kafka 集群由一组代理服务器（三个或更多）组成，这些服务器由唯一的数字 ID 标识。每个代理可以在集群中担任两个角色之一。它可以是领导者经纪人，也可以是追随者经纪人（还有一个特殊的“控制者”角色，我们将在稍后讨论）。

Leader brokers add new records to partitions. A Kafka producer uses the topic name and the partition identifier to determine to which broker it should send the record. We can specify the replication factor of every topic, which tells Kafka how many follower brokers should keep a replica of all partitions that belong to that topic. Of course, it makes no sense to set the number of replicas to a value higher than the number of brokers.领导者经纪人将新记录添加到分区。 Kafka 生产者使用主题名称和分区标识符来确定应将记录发送到哪个代理。我们可以指定每个主题的复制因子，它告诉 Kafka 有多少关注者代理应该保留属于该主题的所有分区的副本。当然，将副本数量设置为高于代理数量的值是没有意义的。

When a producer sends a record to the leader, the producer can specify the acknowledgment level, which describes what must happen before the server can send back a confirmation to notify the producer that the message has been successfully added to the topic.当生产者向领导者发送记录时，生产者可以指定确认级别，该级别描述了服务器可以发回确认以通知生产者消息已成功添加到主题之前必须发生的情况。

If we set zero as the replication level, the producer sends the message and does not wait until it gets any confirmation from the Kafka broker. With the replication level set to one, the producer waits until the leader confirms that it has appended the message to the log.如果我们将复制级别设置为零，则生产者会发送消息，并且不会等到收到 Kafka 代理的任何确认。将复制级别设置为 1 时，生产者会等待，直到领导者确认已将消息附加到日志中。

We can also use the replication level “all,” which means that the min.insync.replicas parameter specifies the number of brokers that must confirm receiving the record before the producer considers it to be successfully delivered.我们还可以使用复制级别“all”，这意味着 min.insync.replicas 参数指定在生产者认为记录已成功交付之前必须确认接收记录的代理数量。

Note that this parameter does not influence the replication level in any way! Even if we set the acknowledgment level to zero, the leader adds the message to its log and forwards it to all replicas. The only difference is the producer’s behavior.请注意，此参数不会以任何方式影响复制级别！即使我们将确认级别设置为零，领导者也会将消息添加到其日志中并将其转发给所有副本。唯一的区别是生产者的行为。

In-sync and out-of-sync replicas同步和不同步副本

Because multiple nodes must communicate with each other, we may get synchronization problems. Partition leaders track the synchronization between themselves and their followers by measuring the replica lag time.由于多个节点必须相互通信，因此我们可能会遇到同步问题。分区领导者通过测量副本滞后时间来跟踪自己与其追随者之间的同步。

By default, a replica is out of sync if it has not requested new messages in 30 seconds, or if it has not caught up to the latest message during the last 30 seconds. We may control the time by setting the replica.lag.time.max.ms parameter.默认情况下，如果副本在 30 秒内未请求新消息，或者在过去 30 秒内未赶上最新消息，则副本不同步。我们可以通过设置replica.lag.time.max.ms参数来控制时间。

The partition leader tracks the number of in-sync replicas because replicating all of the messages across many brokers is crucial to achieving high reliability.分区领导者跟踪同步副本的数量，因为跨多个代理复制所有消息对于实现高可靠性至关重要。

Because of that, if the number of in-sync replicas is lower than the min.insync.replicas parameter, the partition leader prevents any writes to that partition because it cannot guarantee the desired durability.因此，如果同步副本的数量低于 min.insync.replicas 参数，分区领导者会阻止对该分区的任何写入，因为它无法保证所需的持久性。

In the case of data replication, the leader is one of the replicas, so setting the value to 1 means that only the leader must be available. If the parameter equals to two, one follower in-sync broker is required.在数据复制的情况下，领导者是副本之一，因此将该值设置为 1 意味着只有领导者必须可用。如果该参数等于 2，则需要一个跟随者同步代理。

Cluster controller集群控制器

In addition to being a partition leader or a replica, one of the brokers in the cluster is the cluster controller. The controller broker managed partitions, replicas, and performs administrative tasks.除了作为分区领导者或副本之外，集群中的代理之一还是集群控制器。控制器代理管理分区、副本并执行管理任务。

The process of selecting the cluster controller is surprisingly straightforward. The idea is based on the Zookeeper ephemeral nodes feature - a node exists as long as the session that created it is active.选择集群控制器的过程非常简单。这个想法基于 Zookeeper 临时节点功能 - 只要创建它的会话处于活动状态，节点就存在。

When the Kafka cluster starts, every broker attempts to become the controller node. The broker registers as a controller in the Zookeeper, but only the first such operation can succeed. All other brokers receive a notification that a controller already exists.当Kafka集群启动时，每个broker都会尝试成为控制节点。代理在 Zookeeper 中注册为控制器，但只有第一个此类操作才能成功。所有其他代理都会收到控制器已存在的通知。

When the current controller shuts down or gets disconnected from Zookeeper, the controller entry disappears, and all remaining brokers attempt to register as the new controller. Once again, only the first one is going to succeed.当当前控制器关闭或与 Zookeeper 断开连接时，控制器条目消失，所有剩余的代理尝试注册为新控制器。再说一遍，只有第一个才会成功。

Partition leader election分区领导者选举

In a well-balanced cluster, there is no single node that acts as the leader of all partitions. Instead of that, all brokers in the cluster are leaders of some of the partitions and act as replicas of other partitions at the same time.在一个平衡良好的集群中，没有一个节点充当所有分区的领导者。相反，集群中的所有代理都是某些分区的领导者，同时充当其他分区的副本。

Such a distribution of the leader’s responsibilities helps to avoid performance issues caused by heavy load on the leader node. In addition to that, it also allows avoiding costly leader election in case of leader failure.这种领导者职责的分配有助于避免领导者节点负载过重而导致的性能问题。除此之外，它还可以避免在领导者失败的情况下进行代价高昂的领导者选举。

When the administrator creates a new partition, the cluster controller assigns the leadership of this partition to one of the brokers in a way that ensures uniform distribution of partitions across the cluster.当管理员创建新分区时，集群控制器会将该分区的领导权分配给其中一个代理，以确保分区在整个集群中的均匀分布。

We must remember that if the leader broker disconnects from the cluster and then reconnects again, it has only one chance to become the partition leader again. If there are no out-of-sync replicas when the ex-leader reconnects, it can become the partition leader again. If there are such replicas, the current leader remains the partition leader.我们必须记住，如果领导者代理与集群断开连接然后再次重新连接，那么它只有一次机会再次成为分区领导者。如果前领导者重新连接时没有不同步的副本，则它可以再次成为分区领导者。如果存在这样的副本，则当前领导者仍然是分区领导者。

We may enable automatic rebalancing of the cluster, which allows the ex-leader to become the partition leader later when all of the replicas are in-sync again by setting the auto.leader.rebalance.enable parameter. Since 2017, the usage of this parameter was not recommended due to a bug. In some configurations, the cluster tried to rebalance all partitions at once and ended up in a permanent out-of-sync state.我们可以启用集群的自动重新平衡，通过设置 auto.leader.rebalance.enable 参数，当所有副本再次同步时，前领导者可以成为分区领导者。自 2017 年以来，由于存在错误，不建议使用此参数。在某些配置中，集群尝试立即重新平衡所有分区，但最终处于永久不同步状态。

Even in 2020, there is an ongoing discussion in the Jira ticket about this feature, so perhaps some future version of Kafka will offer a working leader rebalancing feature. Before it happens, we must monitor the state of the cluster and use the kafka-reassign-partitions.sh script manually (or automate executing that script if you feel lucky).即使在 2020 年，Jira 票证中仍在持续讨论此功能，因此 Kafka 的未来版本可能会提供工作领导者重新平衡功能。在发生这种情况之前，我们必须监视集群的状态并手动使用 kafka-reassign-partitions.sh 脚本（如果幸运的话，也可以自动执行该脚本）。

Big data大数据 Data engineering数据工程

What are the 4 V's of big data, and which one is the most important?大数据的 4V 是什么？哪一个最重要？

Volume, velocity, variety, and veracity数量、速度、多样性和准确性
Bartosz Mikulski 20 Jan 2020 – 4 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2020 年 1 月 20 日 – 阅读 4 分钟

One of the first models that describe what big data is was the four Vs-model. That definition divides big data into four categories (sometimes called dimensions) of problems: volume, velocity, variety, and veracity.描述大数据的第一个模型是四 V ​​模型。该定义将大数据分为四类（有时称为维度）问题：数量、速度、多样性和准确性。

Volume体积

Volume is the big data dimension that everyone seems to understand intuitively. If it is big, it means we have a lot of it.体量是每个人似乎都能直观理解的大数据维度。如果它很大，就意味着我们有很多。

Volume is all about the number of TB of data you have. This aspect causes problems not only because of the required storage but also the time needed to query the data.容量指的是您拥有的数据的 TB 数量。这方面会导致问题，不仅因为所需的存储空间，而且还因为查询数据所需的时间。

We try to deal with issues caused by high volumes of data by partitioning the files in a way that speeds up queries, building rollups that summarize multiple data points into one, and sampling.我们尝试通过以加速查询的方式对文件进行分区、构建将多个数据点汇总为一个的汇总以及采样来处理由大量数据引起的问题。

Velocity速度

Velocity describes how fast we get new information. Is it 1GB per day, or is it 20 GB per second? Even people who never processed large amounts of data quickly grasp the idea that we cannot use the same code to handle 1GB/day and 20GB/s.速度描述了我们获取新信息的速度。是每天 1GB 还是每秒 20GB？即使是从未处理过大量数据的人也很快就会明白，我们不能使用相同的代码来处理 1GB/天和 20GB/s。

At some point, daily batch processing no longer makes sense, even if the business does not require more updates than once a day. When the velocity gets too high, we start using micro-batching or data streaming.在某些时候，即使业务不需要每天一次以上的更新，每日批处理也不再有意义。当速度太高时，我们开始使用微批处理或数据流。

In the case of real-time data processing, streaming is the only sensible solution. Of course, technically, you can try micro-batching every second. If you have done it and it worked correctly, let me know. I want to hear that story.在实时数据处理的情况下，流式传输是唯一明智的解决方案。当然，从技术上讲，您可以尝试每秒进行微批处理。如果您已完成并且工作正常，请告诉我。我想听那个故事。

Variety种类

What is the data source? We get it from relational databases, document databases, graph databases, XML documents, CSV, logs, and other event streams. There are tons of data sources, and every one of them is different. Note that I listed only data sources that have at least some coarse structure. What about unstructured data?数据来源是什么？我们从关系数据库、文档数据库、图形数据库、XML 文档、CSV、日志和其他事件流中获取它。数据源有很多，而且每个数据源都是不同的。请注意，我仅列出了至少具有一些粗略结构的数据源。那么非结构化数据呢？

Our data pipelines must correctly read data from all of those sources. That requirements cause problems not only because we spend a lot of time writing the code, but also because it needs extensive testing and constant monitoring.我们的数据管道必须正确地从所有这些来源读取数据。这些要求会导致问题，不仅因为我们花费大量时间编写代码，还因为它需要大量测试和持续监控。

Veracity真实性

Speaking of monitoring. How do we know that the data we gathered is useful? Do we have big data or big garbage? Veracity is all about validating the data and checking whether our pipelines produce correct and useful outputs.说到监控。我们如何知道我们收集的数据有用？我们有大数据还是大垃圾？准确性就是验证数据并检查我们的管道是否产生正确且有用的输出。

In my opinion, this is the most critical dimension of big data, and I can easily justify that opinion.在我看来，这是大数据最关键的维度，我可以很容易地证明这个观点是正确的。

What are the six words that will destroy your credibility and jeopardize your career? “This number does not look right.”哪六个词会破坏你的信誉并危及你的职业生涯？ “这个数字看起来不太对劲。”

When you hear it, it is already too late. People don’t trust you anymore. Your co-workers are suspicious about everything you have done so far. Suddenly, you become a person who makes mistakes — the person who was probably feeding us false data for years.当你听到的时候，已经太晚了。人们不再信任你了。您的同事对您迄今为止所做的一切表示怀疑。突然之间，你就变成了一个会犯错误的人——可能多年来一直向我们提供虚假数据的人。

At this point, your supervisor starts to wonder: “why do we even keep him/her here?” After all, being a manager of such a person is not comfortable either. You keep hearing questions like: “How could you let that happen?” “What are you going to do about it?” or “Can we trust your team at all?”此时，您的主管开始怀疑：“为什么我们还要把他/她留在这里？”毕竟，当这样的人的经理，也并不舒服。你不断听到这样的问题：“你怎么能让这种事发生？” “你打算怎么办呢？”或者“我们可以信任你的团队吗？”

If the company makes money and everything is fine, they will probably ask you to fix the problems and let that slide. What if the management made a colossal mistake recently, and the company is on the brink of bankruptcy?如果公司赚钱并且一切都很好，他们可能会要求你解决问题并让事情过去。如果管理层最近犯了一个巨大的错误，公司濒临破产怎么办？

Congratulations, you have been just promoted to the scapegoat position. Everyone in the company will know your name. It may not be your fault, but you will be the one to blame.恭喜你，你刚刚被提升到替罪羊的位置。公司里的每个人都会知道你的名字。这可能不是你的错，但你将是罪魁祸首。

The only good side of the situation is the fact that your suffering will not last for long. Even if the company can’t officially prove that you are the one responsible for problems and fire you, they will make your life miserable and manage you out within the next few months.这种情况唯一好的一面是你的痛苦不会持续太久。即使公司不能正式证明你是问题的责任人并解雇你，他们也会让你的生活变得悲惨，并在接下来的几个月内把你处理掉。

That’s why I think that it does not matter how big your big data is or how fast it grows. It does not matter how many data sources you process. The only important thing is: “can we trust the data?”这就是为什么我认为大数据有多大或者增长有多快并不重要。您处理多少数据源并不重要。唯一重要的是：“我们可以相信这些数据吗？”

Are there more than four Vs?是否有四个以上的 V？

Of course, there are. Dozens of people wanted their share of the fame and invented additional dimensions which names start with V.当然有。许多人想要分享自己的名声，并发明了名称以 V 开头的附加维度。

Some people talk about data “Value.” Those people want you to make sure that the organization is getting value from the data.有些人谈论数据的“价值”。这些人希望您确保组织从数据中获取价值。

Others point out that data constantly changes. Those people describe the changes as the “Variability” dimension. They remind us that we must be ready to constantly improve the validation rules and data source handlers because the structure and the range of correct values continuously change.其他人指出数据不断变化。这些人将这些变化描述为“可变性”维度。他们提醒我们，我们必须准备好不断改进验证规则和数据源处理程序，因为正确值的结构和范围不断变化。

For me, both of those dimensions are extensions of the Veracity dimension. It is all about correctness and keeping the data useful.对我来说，这两个维度都是真实性维度的延伸。这一切都与正确性和保持数据有用有关。

Of course, there are others. I even saw an article “42 V’s of big data.” It is getting ridiculous, really fast.当然，还有其他的。我什至看到了一篇文章“42 V 的大数据”。它变得非常荒谬，速度非常快。

Data Streaming数据流 Data engineering数据工程

Data streaming with Apache Kafka - guide for data engineers使用 Apache Kafka 进行数据流处理 - 数据工程师指南

Are you preparing for a data engineer job interview? Here are my answers to job interview questions about data streaming.您正在准备数据工程师的面试吗？以下是我对有关数据流的求职面试问题的回答。
Bartosz Mikulski 03 Feb 2020 – 12 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2020 年 2 月 3 日 – 阅读 12 分钟

In this article, I am going to describe the fundamental concepts of Apache Kafka. The text should provide answers for data engineers who are considering using Apache Kafka in their infrastructure and to people who are preparing for a data engineering job interview.在本文中，我将描述 Apache Kafka 的基本概念。文本应该为正在考虑在其基础设施中使用 Apache Kafka 的数据工程师以及正在准备数据工程工作面试的人们提供答案。

Message queues消息队列

First, let’s focus on message queues. Why do we use them?首先，让我们关注消息队列。我们为什么使用它们？

Communication between applications应用程序之间的通信

In the case of backend services, we use message queues to decouple applications. When application A receives a request from the user and performs an action, it may send a notification using a message queue. The application B may receive the notification and update its state. Application C may receive the same message and trigger another action as a result.对于后端服务，我们使用消息队列来解耦应用程序。当应用程序 A 接收到来自用户的请求并执行操作时，它可以使用消息队列发送通知。应用程序B可以接收通知并更新其状态。应用程序 C 可能会收到相同的消息并因此触发另一个操作。

In all of those cases, the applications may not be even running when the application A sends the event. There may be more applications that read the same message queue and ignore the message because it is not useful for them.在所有这些情况下，当应用程序 A 发送事​​件时，应用程序甚至可能没有运行。可能有更多的应用程序读取相同的消息队列并忽略该消息，因为它对他们来说没有用。

Most importantly, the programmers who implemented the application A don’t need to know anything about systems that consume their messages.最重要的是，实现应用程序 A 的程序员不需要了解有关使用其消息的系统的任何信息。

They don’t need to provide mocks of their APIs in the tests. They don’t need to implement circuit breakers to protect their application from failures of the dependencies.他们不需要在测试中提供 API 的模拟。他们不需要实现断路器来保护他们的应用程序免受依赖项故障的影响。

In fact, they don’t need to even care about the subsequent actions that are the result of the notification they sent.事实上，他们甚至不需要关心他们发送的通知所导致的后续操作。

Request buffers请求缓冲区

What if we need to send emails to half a million users? Do we send half a million requests to the mailing service? It does not look like a good idea.如果我们需要向 50 万用户发送电子邮件怎么办？我们是否向邮件服务发送了 50 万个请求？这看起来不是一个好主意。

Even if we replicated the service and have enough instances to handle half a million simultaneous requests, something is going to fail. Perhaps an overloaded mailing server is going to be the cause of the failure. Maybe the network is too slow, and some connections are going to timeout.即使我们复制了服务并有足够的实例来处理 50 万个并发请求，某些事情仍然会失败。也许超载的邮件服务器将是失败的原因。可能是网络太慢，有些连接会超时。

We should somehow buffer the requests. Of course, buffering in RAM is always an option. In 2020, half a million requests are not even a lot, so it should not be a problem. Of course, if the service fails for whatever reason, we are going to lose all of the buffered messages.我们应该以某种方式缓冲请求。当然，在 RAM 中缓冲始终是一种选择。 2020 年，50 万个请求甚至不算很多，所以这应该不成问题。当然，如果服务由于某种原因失败，我们将丢失所有缓冲的消息。

In both scenarios, our inability to recover from a failure causes the biggest problem. We can’t just retry sending half a million emails. A failed service may have sent some of the messages successfully, but it did not have an opportunity to report the success.在这两种情况下，我们无法从故障中恢复会导致最大的问题。我们不能只是重试发送 50 万封电子邮件。失败的服务可能已成功发送一些消息，但它没有机会报告成功。

To solve the problem, we use message queues as the request buffer. In our example, the application which wants to send the emails should send them first to the message queue. Message queues are designed to handle a huge load, so it should not be a problem, especially if we are using Apache Kafka.为了解决这个问题，我们使用消息队列作为请求缓冲区。在我们的示例中，想要发送电子邮件的应用程序应该首先将它们发送到消息队列。消息队列设计用于处理巨大的负载，因此这应该不是问题，特别是当我们使用 Apache Kafka 时。

In this setup, we have another service (or a group of them) that read messages from the message queue and send the email.在此设置中，我们有另一个服务（或一组）从消息队列中读取消息并发送电子邮件。

If something fails, we have a few options. We can stop processing at the first failure and investigate the problem. The messages in the queue can wait until we fix it. We can also store the error somewhere (perhaps in another queue) and continue sending messages. In the end, we may try to resend the failed messages.如果出现问题，我们有几种选择。我们可以在第一次失败时停止处理并调查问题。队列中的消息可以等待我们修复它。我们还可以将错误存储在某个地方（可能在另一个队列中）并继续发送消息。最后，我们可能会尝试重新发送失败的消息。

Of course, we may resend an email that was successfully sent, but we failed to report the success. In that case, some people may receive duplicates. It is not a significant risk if we send duplicates to a few people. If the user complains, we can always apologize. Try apologizing to half a million users ;)当然，我们可能会重新发送已成功发送的电子邮件，但未能报告成功。在这种情况下，有些人可能会收到重复的邮件。如果我们将副本发送给少数人，这并不是一个重大风险。如果用户投诉，我们随时可以道歉。尝试向 50 万用户道歉；）

Data synchronization数据同步

It is not a usual use-case of message queues, but Apache Kafka offers Connect API, which we can configure to propagate changes from one database to another automatically. We are not limited to databases! It is possible to write a Connect API implementation that reads from/writes to a REST API endpoint, Amazon S3, or other queues.这不是消息队列的常见用例，但 Apache Kafka 提供了 Connect API，我们可以将其配置为自动将更改从一个数据库传播到另一个数据库。我们不仅限于数据库！可以编写一个 Connect API 实现来读取/写入 REST API 终端节点、Amazon S3 或其他队列。

If the implementation we need is not already available in Maven or a GitHub repository, we can quickly implement a new Source, Sink, or Transformation (yes, it is possible to apply data transformations in the queue).如果我们需要的实现在 Maven 或 GitHub 存储库中尚不可用，我们可以快速实现新的 Source、Sink 或 Transformation（是的，可以在队列中应用数据转换）。

This feature is particularly useful for data engineers because we routinely synchronize data between multiple databases or applications.此功能对于数据工程师特别有用，因为我们通常会在多个数据库或应用程序之间同步数据。

Real-time data aggregation实时数据聚合

Finally, the most interesting use-case. Why do we bother with data streaming? Of course, because we want real-time data! Not just all of the data. That would be useless. We want a data aggregation that gets updated in real-time.最后，最有趣的用例。为什么我们要为数据流烦恼？当然，因为我们想要实时数据！不仅仅是所有数据。那就没用了。我们想要实时更新的数据聚合。

With Apache Kafka, we have two options. We can implement an application that reads from a Kafka topic and aggregates the data, for example, a Spark Streaming application. Alternatively, we can use KSQL - a specialized SQL-like language that allows us to query the data stream without writing code.对于 Apache Kafka，我们有两种选择。我们可以实现一个从 Kafka 主题读取并聚合数据的应用程序，例如 Spark Streaming 应用程序。或者，我们可以使用 KSQL——一种专门的类似 SQL 的语言，它允许我们在不编写代码的情况下查询数据流。

What about the results? We have Kafka Connect API, so we can aggregate a data stream using KSQL, send the aggregation to a separate Kafka topic, and, finally, write the results into a database or send it to a REST API.结果怎么样？我们有 Kafka Connect API，因此我们可以使用 KSQL 聚合数据流，将聚合发送到单独的 Kafka 主题，最后将结果写入数据库或将其发送到 REST API。

Apache Kafka architecture阿帕奇卡夫卡架构

Now, when we know why we may want to use Apache Kafka, let’s have a look at its building blocks.现在，当我们知道为什么要使用 Apache Kafka 时，让我们看看它的构建块。

Kafka queues are implemented as an indexed append-only log. Because of that, multiple readers can retrieve messages from the queue at the same time. Every reader may start reading at a different index, so it is not required to start at the beginning of the queue or the most recent message.Kafka 队列被实现为索引附加日志。因此，多个读者可以同时从队列中检索消息。每个读者都可以从不同的索引开始阅读，因此不需要从队列的开头或最新的消息开始。

The queue is append-only, so messages don’t disappear when a reader retrieves them (but we can specify the retention settings to remove old messages). Also, Kafka tracks what messages have been read by the clients, so the consumer may choose to continue reading the queue from the last received message or reset the offset and start from the beginning or any arbitrary position in the data stream.队列是仅追加的，因此当读者检索消息时消息不会消失（但我们可以指定保留设置以删除旧消息）。此外，Kafka 会跟踪客户端读取了哪些消息，因此消费者可以选择从最后收到的消息继续读取队列，或者重置偏移量并从数据流的开头或任意位置开始。

Topics主题

The most fundamental part of Apache Kafka is the concept of topics. Everybody who has ever used a messaging service should intuitively understand what the topic is. People not familiar with that may think of a topic as the identifier of a data stream.Apache Kafka 最基本的部分是主题的概念。每个曾经使用过消息服务的人都应该直观地了解该主题是什么。不熟悉这一点的人可能会认为主题是数据流的标识符。

At any given time, there may be multiple topics on Kafka servers. The messages written to a topic get replicated between multiple nodes of a Kafka cluster to ensure that we don’t lose data in case of a failure.在任何给定时间，Kafka 服务器上都可能有多个主题。写入主题的消息会在 Kafka 集群的多个节点之间复制，以确保在发生故障时不会丢失数据。

The consumers subscribe to a topic to get messages. In KSQL, topics may be used as the output of a query and in the FROM and JOIN clauses.消费者订阅一个主题来获取消息。在 KSQL 中，主题可以用作查询的输出以及 FROM 和 JOIN 子句中。

Obviously, producers of messages have to specify the topic. In the Connect API, it is possible to change the destination topic by using a Transformer that extracts the new topic name from the message. For example, the io.confluent.connect.transforms.ExtractTopic Transformer provided by Confluent implements such a behavior.显然，消息的生产者必须指定主题。在 Connect API 中，可以使用从消息中提取新主题名称的转换器来更改目标主题。例如，Confluence 提供的 io.confluence.connect.transforms.ExtractTopic Transformer 就实现了这样的行为。

Partitions分区

In almost every data engineering project, topics are not enough. We need to split the topic into partitions because that allows us to parallelize message consumption by connecting multiple consumers to the same topic. In this case, every consumer reads messages that belong to a single partition.几乎在每个数据工程项目中，仅有主题是不够的。我们需要将主题拆分为多个分区，因为这允许我们通过将多个消费者连接到同一主题来并行化消息消费。在这种情况下，每个消费者都会读取属于单个分区的消息。

The producers of messages should specify the partition key. Kafka calculates a hash function using the partition key as the input. The output of the hash function (a number) is used to assign the message to a partition.消息的生产者应指定分区键。 Kafka 使用分区键作为输入来计算哈希函数。哈希函数的输出（数字）用于将消息分配给分区。

It is possible to publish messages to a partitioned topic without specifying the partition key, but it is not recommended. The Kafka’s default behavior in case of a missing partition key is suboptimal.可以在不指定分区键的情况下将消息发布到分区主题，但不建议这样做。缺少分区键时 Kafka 的默认行为不是最优的。

Skewed partitions倾斜的分区

Optimal parallelization requires more than specifying a partitioning key. If the output of the Kafka’s hash function is not uniformly distributed, we are going to end up with skewed partitions. It is a situation in which one partition receives more messages than the others. Skewed partitions lead to the unbalanced workload of the message consumers.最佳并行化需要的不仅仅是指定分区键。如果 Kafka 哈希函数的输出不是均匀分布的，我们最终会得到倾斜的分区。这是一种情况，其中一个分区比其他分区接收到更多消息。倾斜的分区会导致消息消费者的工作负载不平衡。

We can solve that problem by changing the partitioning key to a value that gives us a uniformly distributed output after hashing. If there is no better option, a random number should give us optimal partitioning.我们可以通过将分区键更改为一个值来解决该问题，该值在散列后为我们提供均匀分布的输出。如果没有更好的选择，随机数应该为我们提供最佳划分。

In addition to subpar hashing, we may face problems caused by slow consumers. In this case, the messages may be uniformly distributed across all partitions, but one of the consumers is slower than the others.除了低于标准的散列之外，我们还可能面临消费者缓慢造成的问题。在这种情况下，消息可能均匀分布在所有分区上，但其中一个消费者比其他消费者慢。

It is best to fix such issues by optimizing the consumer’s code or adding more partitions. Alternatively, it is possible to tweak the partitioning key until we get the desired distribution, but that solution feels like monkey-patching.最好通过优化消费者的代码或添加更多分区来解决此类问题。或者，可以调整分区键，直到获得所需的分布，但该解决方案感觉就像猴子修补。

Note: In some cases, we may want skewed partitioning because it is the only way to get the correct results! It may be the case if Kafka is used for event sourcing, and every consumer deals with only a subset of messages.注意：在某些情况下，我们可能需要倾斜分区，因为这是获得正确结果的唯一方法！如果 Kafka 用于事件源，并且每个消费者仅处理消息的子集，则可能会出现这种情况。

For example, all users whose names start with A-C are handled by the same consumer and other consumers don’t store their data. In such a situation, we need stable hashing that permanently assigns a user to a partition.例如，名称以 A-C 开头的所有用户都由同一个消费者处理，其他消费者不存储他们的数据。在这种情况下，我们需要稳定的哈希来将用户永久分配到分区。

Stream-Table Duality流表对偶性

It seems strange, but a data stream and a table are the same. We may interpret a stream of updates as a table - we call it event-sourcing. At the same time, we may interpret a table as a stream - every update of the table’s content is a new event.看起来很奇怪，但是数据流和表是一样的。我们可以将更新流解释为一个表——我们称之为事件溯源。同时，我们可以将表解释为流——表内容的每次更新都是一个新事件。

In Kafka, we have a concept of KTables, which are a materialized view of the updates sent to a Kafka topic. We may use them to look up the “current” state of data records by their key.在 Kafka 中，我们有一个 KTable 的概念，它是发送到 Kafka 主题的更新的物化视图。我们可以使用它们通过键来查找数据记录的“当前”状态。

The concept of Stream-Table Duality is the basis of using Kafka Connect API to synchronize data between databases. We turn one database into a stream of data updates, transport it with Kafka, and apply the updates to another database.流表二元性的概念是使用Kafka Connect API在数据库之间同步数据的基础。我们将一个数据库转换为数据更新流，使用 Kafka 进行传输，并将更新应用到另一个数据库。

Offset抵消

The offset is a sequential id number that uniquely identifies each record within the partition. As I wrote before, Kafka keeps the offset metadata for every consumer, but the consumer may change it to an arbitrary value.偏移量是一个连续的 ID 号，唯一标识分区内的每个记录。正如我之前所写，Kafka 为每个消费者保留偏移量元数据，但消费者可以将其更改为任意值。

This ability allows us to reprocess parts of the data stream in case of errors. We can even use stream reprocessing as a debugging tool and replay the stream of events to see what happens.这种能力使我们能够在出现错误时重新处理部分数据流。我们甚至可以使用流重新处理作为调试工具并重播事件流以查看发生了什么。

Consumers and consumer groups消费者和消费群体

We must label all Kafka topic consumers with a consumer group. Kafka uses the consumer group to determine whether the topic partitions should be load-balanced over the consumer instances or whether all consumers get all of the data.我们必须用消费者组来标记所有 Kafka 主题消费者。 Kafka 使用消费者组来确定主题分区是否应在消费者实例上进行负载平衡，或者是否所有消费者都获取所有数据。

If multiple consumers use the same consumer group name, Kafka load-balances the topic, and every consumer within the group received messages from only a subset of partitions.如果多个消费者使用相同的消费者组名称，Kafka 会对主题进行负载平衡，并且组内的每个消费者仅从分区子集接收消息。

Of course, a consumer cannot get a fraction of a partition, so it is not possible to have more consumers than partitions. If we have more consumers than partitions, some of them not do anything and just wait as a backup for the working consumers.当然，消费者无法获得分区的一小部分，因此不可能拥有比分区更多的消费者。如果我们的消费者多于分区，那么其中一些消费者不会执行任何操作，只是等待作为工作消费者的备份。

Kafka provides a total order over messages within one partition. Because of that, messages that ended up in separate partitions may be consumed in a different order than their publication order.Kafka 提供一个分区内消息的全序。因此，最终位于不同分区的消息可能会以与其发布顺序不同的顺序被使用。

If a total order of all messages within one topic is required, we must use only one partition per topic. Of course, in this case, we can have only one consumer within a consumer group.如果需要一个主题内所有消息的总顺序，则每个主题只能使用一个分区。当然，在这种情况下，一个消费者组中只能有一个消费者。

KSQLKSQL

KSQL is a SQL-like language that allows us to implement stream transformations within Kafka. It can read events from a stream and join them with events from another stream. Of course, in the case of streams, we join over a window, not the entire dataset. As a result, KSQL produces events that are published on a topic.KSQL 是一种类似 SQL 的语言，允许我们在 Kafka 中实现流转换。它可以从流中读取事件并将它们与另一个流中的事件连接起来。当然，在流的情况下，我们在一个窗口上连接，而不是整个数据集。因此，KSQL 会生成在某个主题上发布的事件。

KSQL is NOT a part of Apache Kafka. We can install KSQL servers on a separate cluster, so failures of KSQL nodes do not affect Kafka nodes.KSQL 不是 Apache Kafka 的一部分。我们可以将KSQL服务器安装在单独的集群上，这样KSQL节点的故障不会影响Kafka节点。

KSQL server consists of a KSQL engine that runs the stream processing and a REST API server that allows communication with the KSQL client.KSQL 服务器由运行流处理的 KSQL 引擎和允许与 KSQL 客户端通信的 REST API 服务器组成。

Note that KSQL works as a continuous query system on a data stream. It is built on top of the Kafka Streams library, so it is a good fit when we have to transform, aggregate, join stream data. It is NOT a business intelligence application or a debugging tool for Kafka topics.请注意，KSQL 作为数据流上的连续查询系统运行。它构建在 Kafka Streams 库之上，因此当我们必须转换、聚合、连接流数据时，它非常适合。它不是商业智能应用程序或 Kafka 主题的调试工具。

Apache Kafka performance tuning for big dataApache Kafka 大数据性能调优

I have already mentioned skewed partitions, which are one of the most common causes of performance problems in Apache Kafka.我已经提到过倾斜分区，这是 Apache Kafka 性能问题的最常见原因之一。

In addition to that, we should make sure that we have enough consumers to process all partitions. It makes no sense to split data into 10 partitions just to consume it with 8 consumers. Some of them will get more than one partition and lag behind the others.除此之外，我们应该确保有足够的消费者来处理所有分区。将数据拆分为 10 个分区只是为了让 8 个消费者使用它是没有意义的。其中一些将获得多个分区并落后于其他分区。

In the case of producers, we must know that producers buffer events before sending them to Kafka.对于生产者来说，我们必须知道生产者在将事件发送到 Kafka 之前会对其进行缓冲。

It takes more time to send multiple small messages over the network than to send one large message that consists of multiple events. Because of that, we should ensure that the buffer is big enough.通过网络发送多条小消息比发送一条包含多个事件的大消息花费更多时间。因此，我们应该确保缓冲区足够大。

Of course, buffering messages adds latency between message publication and actual transmission over the network, so it is a tradeoff between sending small messages more often or waiting to send a large one.当然，缓冲消息会增加消息发布和通过网络实际传输之间的延迟，因此这是更频繁地发送小消息或等待发送大消息之间的权衡。

Data engineering数据工程

What is the difference between data lake, data warehouse, and data mart数据湖、数据仓库和数据集市有什么区别

We can easily distinguish between them by focusing on three qualities: data structure (schema), data quality, and ownership.我们可以通过关注三个质量来轻松区分它们：数据结构（模式）、数据质量和所有权。
Bartosz Mikulski 18 Dec 2019 – 2 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2019 年 12 月 18 日 – 阅读 2 分钟

We are building some data infrastructure, but what is it? What is the proper name of that thing? In IT, we usually have big problems with naming concepts, so there is no surprise that we ended up with three very similar names to describe ideas that are fundamentally different.我们正在建设一些数据基础设施，但它是什么？那东西的正确名称是什么？在 IT 领域，我们通常在命名概念时遇到很大的问题，因此我们最终用三个非常相似的名称来描述根本不同的想法也就不足为奇了。

There are at least three differences between data lakes, data marts, and data warehouses. We can easily distinguish between them by focusing on three qualities: data structure (schema), data quality, and ownership.数据湖、数据集市和数据仓库之间至少存在三个区别。我们可以通过关注三个质量来轻松区分它们：数据结构（模式）、数据质量和所有权。

Data warehouse数据仓库

Typically, a data warehouse is a centralized database used for analytics. When we design a data warehouse, we usually have some knowledge about the queries we need to execute in that database, so we prepare the schema specifically for that kind of usage. Because of that, we usually decide to use denormalized schemas, for example, the snowflake of the star schema.通常，数据仓库是用于分析的集中式数据库。当我们设计数据仓库时，我们通常对需要在该数据库中执行的查询有一些了解，因此我们专门为这种用途准备模式。因此，我们通常决定使用非规范化模式，例如星型模式的雪花。

We expect that a data warehouse contains data that is “ready to use,” so the data loaded into the data warehouse is already validated and preprocessed. Often, we assume that the data warehouse is the “single source of truth” and always contains correct values.我们期望数据仓库包含“随时可用”的数据，因此加载到数据仓库中的数据已经过验证和预处理。通常，我们假设数据仓库是“单一事实来源”并且始终包含正确的值。

Data lake数据湖

In the case of a data lake, we have a centralized storage of raw data. Typically, multiple transformations process the same raw data, so we end up with many data structures derived from the same source. The primary purpose of a data lake is to have everything in one place to make it easy to join multiple data sources.就数据湖而言，我们有原始数据的集中存储。通常，多个转换处理相同的原始数据，因此我们最终会得到来自同一源的许多数据结构。数据湖的主要目的是将所有内容集中在一处，以便轻松连接多个数据源。

It is common to validate the data lake content at the time when the data is used, not when it is loaded into the data lake. On the one hand, that causes data quality problems because there may be multiple validation pipelines that are not compatible with each other. But on the other hand, it allows defining what “valid” means in every data transformation (after all, it does not need to mean the same for everyone).通常在使用数据时验证数据湖内容，而不是在将数据加载到数据湖时验证数据湖内容。一方面，这会导致数据质量问题，因为可能存在多个彼此不兼容的验证管道。但另一方面，它允许在每个数据转换中定义“有效”的含义（毕竟，它不需要对每个人都意味着相同）。

Data mart数据库

A data mart is easy to define. It is just a decentralized version of the data warehouse. Instead of building one large system for the whole company, we create smaller analytics tools for every department.数据集市很容易定义。它只是数据仓库的去中心化版本。我们没有为整个公司构建一个大型系统，而是为每个部门创建较小的分析工具。

That kind of design allows us to apply the domain-driven development concepts to data storage. We can isolate domains, define concept names based on the domain-specific ubiquitous language, and not worry about multiple definitions of the same name.这种设计使我们能够将领域驱动开发概念应用于数据存储。我们可以隔离领域，根据特定领域的通用语言定义概念名称，而不用担心同一个名称的多个定义。

Three biggest traps to avoid while setting Spark executor memory设置 Spark 执行器内存时要避免的三个最大陷阱

Apache Spark is wasting a lot of RAM!Apache Spark 浪费了大量 RAM！
Bartosz Mikulski 16 Dec 2019 – 1 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2019 年 12 月 16 日 – 阅读 1 分钟

What happens when you set the executor memory of a Spark worker which uses YARN as the cluster resource manager? Does it get exactly the amount of memory you requested? Unfortunately, no.当您设置使用 YARN 作为集群资源管理器的 Spark Worker 的执行程序内存时会发生什么？它是否准确地获得了您请求的内存量？很不幸的是，不行。

To makes things easy to comprehend, imagine that I have a Spark cluster with a small amount of memory. Let’s say I have 16GB of RAM.为了使事情易于理解，假设我有一个具有少量内存的 Spark 集群。假设我有 16GB 的 RAM。

I want to run a Spark job that requires 4GB of memory. What is going to happen? Will YARN allocate 4GB for that Spark job?我想运行需要 4GB 内存的 Spark 作业。将会发生什么？ YARN 会为 Spark 作业分配 4GB 空间吗？

spark.executor.memoryOverheadSpark.executor.memoryOverhead

First, it is going to read the spark.executor.memoryOverhead parameter and multiply the requested amount of memory by the overhead value (by default, 10%, with a minimum of 384 MB).首先，它将读取spark.executor.memoryOverhead参数，并将请求的内存量乘以开销值（默认为10%，最小为384 MB）。

Spark will add the overhead to the executor memory and, as a consequence, request 4506 MB of memory.Spark 会增加执行程序内存的开销，因此会请求 4506 MB 的内存。

yarn.scheduler.minimum-allocation-mb纱线.scheduler.最小分配-mb

The yarn.scheduler.minimum-allocation-mb parameter causes the second problem.该yarn.scheduler.minimum-allocation-mb参数导致第二个问题。

I set the minimal allocation to 4GB, so YARN will always allocate at least 4GB for every Spark job. That is fine, but YARN can assign only the multiple of the minimum-allocation-mb value.我将最小分配设置为 4GB，因此 YARN 始终会为每个 Spark 作业分配至少 4GB。这很好，但 YARN 只能分配最小分配 mb 值的倍数。

If yarn.scheduler.minimum-allocation-mb is set to 4 GB and I have 16GB of available memory, YARN can allocate 4GB, 8GB, 12GB, or 16GB.如果yarn.scheduler.minimum-allocation-mb设置为4 GB并且我有16GB可用内存，则YARN可以分配4GB，8GB，12GB或16GB。

So what is going to happen when Spark requests 4506MB of memory? YARN allocates 8GB! That is a huge amount of additional memory!那么当 Spark 请求 4506MB 内存时会发生什么呢？ YARN分配8GB！这是大量的额外内存！

spark.executor.memorySpark.executor.内存

Why is this a problem? Because Spark will never use that additional memory!为什么这是个问题？因为 Spark 永远不会使用额外的内存！

The spark.executor.memory parameter gets passed to the Java process running Spark and limits its memory usage. I have allocated 8GB of memory, but I can access only half of it! I am wasting a lot of RAM!Spark.executor.memory 参数传递给运行 Spark 的 Java 进程并限制其内存使用。我分配了8GB内存，但我只能访问一半！我浪费了很多内存！

Apache Spark阿帕奇火花 Data engineering数据工程

Apache Spark: should we use RDD, Dataset, or DataFrame?Apache Spark：我们应该使用 RDD、Dataset 还是 DataFrame？

Is there a difference between Dataset and DataFrame? Why do we even have both?数据集和数据帧有区别吗？为什么我们两者都有？
Bartosz Mikulski 04 Dec 2019 – 3 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2019 年 12 月 4 日 – 阅读时间 3 分钟

I remember having a problem deciding which data type I should use in my Spark code. I knew that RDDs are not optimized, but what is the difference between Dataset and DataFrame? Why do we even have both?我记得在决定 Spark 代码中应使用哪种数据类型时遇到了问题。我知道 RDD 没有优化，但是 Dataset 和 DataFrame 有什么区别？为什么我们两者都有？

In this article, I am going to show you why you should not use RDDs directly, why Datasets are the best, and why you should not bother about DataFrames.在本文中，我将向您展示为什么不应该直接使用 RDD、为什么数据集是最好的以及为什么您不应该担心 DataFrame。

Why shouldn’t we use RDDs?为什么我们不应该使用 RDD？

The biggest problem of RDDs is the fact that Spark can not optimize the code. It is not possible because RDDs provide only low-level API. The code we write does not express the result we want, but instead, we must provide detailed step-by-step instructions.RDD最大的问题是Spark无法优化代码。这是不可能的，因为 RDD 只提供低级 API。我们编写的代码并不能表达我们想要的结果，而是必须提供详细的分步说明。

Such an API is quite useful when we are dealing with unstructured data. In that case, it is usually not a huge problem. After all, Spark will not optimize the processing of audio or image data, and we are not going to do any aggregations on such kind of data.当我们处理非结构化数据时，这样的 API 非常有用。在这种情况下，通常不是一个大问题。毕竟，Spark不会优化音频或图像数据的处理，我们也不会对此类数据进行任何聚合。

If we can extract some useful structure from the unstructured data, it is often beneficial to convert the RDDs into Datasets or DataFrames and continue processing using the SQL-like code to get at least some of the optimizations.如果我们可以从非结构化数据中提取一些有用的结构，那么将 RDD 转换为数据集或数据帧并使用类似 SQL 的代码继续处理以获得至少一些优化通常是有益的。

How does Spark optimize code?Spark如何优化代码？

  1. When we write our Spark code using DataFrames, Datasets, or SQL queries, it gets converted into an Unresolved Logic Plan.当我们使用 DataFrame、数据集或 SQL 查询编写 Spark 代码时，它会转换为未解析的逻辑计划。

  2. Every DataFrame and Dataset represents a logical table with data. Spark has a catalog of used tables and columns. That information allows it to resolve references between tables and create a Logical Plan of the query.每个 DataFrame 和 Dataset 都代表一个包含数据的逻辑表。 Spark 有一个已用表和列的目录。该信息允许它解析表之间的引用并创建查询的逻辑计划。

  3. At this point, the Catalyst optimizer produces the Optimized Logical Plan.此时，Catalyst 优化器会生成优化逻辑计划。

  4. Spark knows which worker nodes have the required partitions of data so it can use the Optimized Logical Plan to produce a Psychical Plan. There are multiple ways of converting the logical plan into a psychical plan, so this operation returns multiple psychical plans.Spark 知道哪些工作节点具有所需的数据分区，因此它可以使用优化逻辑计划来生成心理计划。将逻辑计划转换为心理计划的方法有多种，因此此操作会返回多个心理计划。

  5. Spark estimates the cost of every psychical plan and selects the most optimal one.Spark 会估算每个心理计划的成本并选择最佳的一个。

  6. The Selected Psychical Plan gets transformed into optimal RDD operations. That code gets executed by the worker nodes.选定的心理计划转化为最佳 RDD 操作。该代码由工作节点执行。

Why are Datasets the best?为什么数据集是最好的？

Datasets provide two features that are required to produce the most optimal query execution plan:数据集提供了生成最佳查询执行计划所需的两个功能：

First, Datasets are defined as SQL-like operations, so we are not telling Spark what is supposed to happen, but instead of that, we declare what the expected outcome is. Therefore, the optimizer can modify the code to get the desired result most optimally.首先，数据集被定义为类似 SQL 的操作，因此我们不会告诉 Spark 应该发生什么，而是声明预期结果是什么。因此，优化器可以修改代码以获得最佳的期望结果。

In addition to that, a Dataset has its schema. The schema defines the column names and their types. The schema allows Spark to not only apply type-specific optimizations but also check whether the query is correct before it gets executed.除此之外，数据集还有其模式。该架构定义了列名称及其类型。该模式不仅允许 Spark 应用特定于类型的优化，还可以在执行查询之前检查查询是否正确。

Because of that, we are going to get an error message sooner. It is always good to see information about a missing column before Spark starts executing the query, not after waiting for six hours to get the result.因此，我们会更快收到错误消息。在 Spark 开始执行查询之前看到有关缺失列的信息总是好的，而不是在等待六个小时才能获得结果之后。

What about DataFrames?数据框呢？

type DataFrame = Dataset[Row]

Since Spark 2.0, Datasets and DataFrames have been unified. Now, DataFrames are defined as Datasets of type Row. I chose to pretend that DataFrames don’t exist anymore ;)从Spark 2.0开始，Datasets和DataFrames已经统一。现在，DataFrame 被定义为 Row 类型的数据集。我选择假装 DataFrame 不再存在；）

Dependencies between DAGs: How to wait until another DAG finishes in Airflow?DAG 之间的依赖关系：如何等待另一个 DAG 在 Airflow 中完成？

How to trigger Airflow DAG when another DAG is completed当另一个 DAG 完成时如何触发 Airflow DAG
Bartosz Mikulski 17 Jul 2019 – 2 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2019 年 7 月 17 日 – 阅读 2 分钟

In this article, I am going to show how to set up dependencies between two DAGs. Imagine that I have a DAG that dumps data from production databases and another DAG that aggregates the raw data and pushes the result into a reporting database.在本文中，我将展示如何在两个 DAG 之间设置依赖关系。想象一下，我有一个从生产数据库转储数据的 DAG，以及另一个聚合原始数据并将结果推送到报告数据库中的 DAG。

I want the second DAG to run when the first one finishes, but I don’t want to move its tasks into the first DAG because that would make a mess in the configuration.我希望第二个 DAG 在第一个 DAG 完成时运行，但我不想将其任务移至第一个 DAG 中，因为这会使配置变得混乱。

Airflow does not allow to set up dependencies between DAGs explicitly, but we can use Sensors to postpone the start of the second DAG until the first one successfully finishes.Airflow 不允许显式设置 DAG 之间的依赖关系，但我们可以使用传感器推迟第二个 DAG 的启动，直到第一个 DAG 成功完成。

ExternalTaskSensor外部任务传感器

To configure the sensor, we need the identifier of another DAG (we will wait until that DAG finishes). Additionally, we can also specify the identifier of a task within the DAG (if we want to wait for a single task). If we want to wait for the whole DAG we must set external_task_id = None.要配置传感器，我们需要另一个 DAG 的标识符（我们将等到该 DAG 完成）。此外，我们还可以指定 DAG 中任务的标识符（如果我们想等待单个任务）。如果我们想等待整个 DAG，我们必须设置 external_task_id = None。

from datetime import datetime
from airflow import DAG
from airflow.operators.dummy_operator import DummyOperator
from airflow.sensors.external_task_sensor import ExternalTaskSensor

dag = DAG('dependency_dag', description='DAG with sensor', schedule_interval='* * * * *',
          start_date=datetime(2019, 7, 10))

sensor = ExternalTaskSensor(task_id='dag_sensor', external_dag_id = 'another_dag_id', external_task_id = None, dag=dag, mode = 'reschedule')

task = DummyOperator(task_id='some_task', retries=1, dag=dag)

task.set_upstream(sensor)

By default, the sensor waits for the successful execution of the dependency on the current day. We can also specify the status and time delta, so it is possible to run a dependency when a DAG fails or run it every hour. For details, look at the allowed_states and execution_delta parameters in the documentation.默认情况下，传感器等待当天成功执行依赖项。我们还可以指定状态和时间增量，因此可以在 DAG 失败时运行依赖项或每小时运行一次。有关详细信息，请查看文档中的 allowed_states 和execution_delta 参数。

How to use sensors如何使用传感器

The sensor is just another type of task, so I create a new DAG which begins with a sensor. In the default configuration, the sensor checks the dependency status every minute.传感器只是另一种类型的任务，因此我创建了一个以传感器开始的新 DAG。在默认配置中，传感器每分钟检查依赖性状态。

After I configure the sensor, I should specify the rest of the tasks in the DAG. As I wrote in the previous paragraph, we use sensors like regular tasks, so I connect the task with the sensor using the upstream/downstream operator. I do it in the last line:配置传感器后，我应该指定 DAG 中的其余任务。正如我在上一段中所写的，我们像常规任务一样使用传感器，因此我使用上游/下游运算符将任务与传感器连接起来。我在最后一行这样做：

task.set_upstream(sensor)

How to run Airflow in Docker (with a persistent database)如何在 Docker 中运行 Airflow（带有持久数据库）

How to configure Airflow in a Docker container如何在 Docker 容器中配置 Airflow
Bartosz Mikulski 15 Jul 2019 – 1 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2019 年 7 月 15 日 – 阅读 1 分钟

In this blog post, I am going to show you how to prepare the minimalist setup of puckel/docker-airflow Docker image that will run a single DAG and store logs persistently (so we will not lose it during restarts of Docker container).在这篇博文中，我将向您展示如何准备 puckel/docker-airflow Docker 映像的极简设置，该映像将运行单个 DAG 并持久存储日志（这样我们就不会在 Docker 容器重新启动期间丢失它）。

Firstly, we have to pull the Docker image and prepare the minimalist DAG configuration. The simplest DAG consists of a single DummyOperator. The content of the file is listed below:首先，我们必须拉取 Docker 映像并准备简约的 DAG 配置。最简单的 DAG 由单个 DummyOperator 组成。该文件的内容如下：

from datetime import datetime

          schedule_interval='0 12 * * *',
          start_date=datetime(2019, 7, 10))

dummy_operator = DummyOperator(task_id='dummy_task', retries=1, dag=dag)

I am going to save the code in minimalist.py file in the /home/user/airflow/dags directory (you will need the full path to the directory where you saved the file).我将把代码保存在 /home/user/airflow/dags 目录中的minimalist.py 文件中（您将需要保存文件的目录的完整路径）。

To pass the DAG configuration to the Airflow instance we need to map the local directory to a directory in a Docker container using the volume configuration, so we have to add those parameters to docker run parameters:要将 DAG 配置传递到 Airflow 实例，我们需要使用卷配置将本地目录映射到 Docker 容器中的目录，因此我们必须将这些参数添加到 docker run 参数中：

-v /home/user/airflow/dags:/usr/local/airflow/dags

By default, the log database is in the /usr/local/airflow/airflow.db file. I cannot map the /usr/local/airflow directory to a local directory, because that would break the configuration (the whole configuration is there, and I don’t want to override it).默认情况下，日志数据库位于 /usr/local/airflow/airflow.db 文件中。我无法将 /usr/local/airflow 目录映射到本地目录，因为这会破坏配置（整个配置都在那里，我不想覆盖它）。

To deal with that problem, I have to change the location of the database file. That can be done using an environment variable: AIRFLOW__CORE__SQL_ALCHEMY_CONN:为了解决这个问题，我必须更改数据库文件的位置。这可以使用环境变量来完成：AIRFLOW__CORE__SQL_ALCHEMY_CONN：

I am going to change it to sqlite:////usr/local/airflow/db/airflow.db (note that it has to be the full SQL connection string), using this parameter:我将使用以下参数将其更改为 sqlite:////usr/local/airflow/db/airflow.db （注意它必须是完整的 SQL 连接字符串）：

-e AIRFLOW__CORE__SQL_ALCHEMY_CONN=sqlite:////usr/local/airflow/db/airflow.db

After that change, I have to map the directory I choose to another local directory.更改后，我必须将我选择的目录映射到另一个本地目录。

-v /home/user/airflow/db:/usr/local/airflow/db

The full command that runs Airflow in Docker with custom dags and persisted log is here:在 Docker 中使用自定义 dags 和持久日志运行 Airflow 的完整命令如下：

docker run -d -p 8080:8080 -e AIRFLOW__CORE__SQL_ALCHEMY_CONN=sqlite:////usr/local/airflow/db/airflow.db -v /home/user/airflow/dags:/usr/local/airflow/dags -v /home/user/airflow/db:/usr/local/airflow/db puckel/docker-airflow webserver

Remember to change this part: /home/user/airflow/ to the full path of your local directory (in both parameters).请记住将这部分： /home/user/airflow/ 更改为本地目录的完整路径（在两个参数中）。

How Airflow scheduler worksAirflow 调度程序的工作原理

Explanation of the Airflow interval and start_date parametersAirflow Interval 和 start_date 参数的说明
Bartosz Mikulski 12 Apr 2019 – 1 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2019 年 4 月 12 日 – 阅读 1 分钟

Do you think that Airflow scheduler is unintuitive? Have you tried to use intervals and the only method that worked was “trial and error?” Does it look like the only way to set it up correctly is tweaking the settings until somehow you get it right? If yes, this is a blog post for you ;)您是否认为 Airflow 调度程序不直观？您是否尝试过使用间隔，而唯一有效的方法是“反复试验”？看起来正确设置的唯一方法是调整设置，直到以某种方式正确设置为止吗？如果是的话，这是一篇适合您的博客文章；）

I am going to explain the Airflow scheduler and maybe, just maybe, help you understand how it works.我将解释 Airflow 调度程序，也许，只是也许，帮助您理解它是如何工作的。

Example例子

Imagine that Airflow is a person with a timer. Usually, we use Airflow to move data around, and recently I published summaries of the Data Janitor talks, so let’s assume that Airflow is a janitor.想象一下 Airflow 是一个有计时器的人。通常，我们使用 Airflow 来移动数据，最近我发布了 Data Janitor 演讲的摘要，所以我们假设 Airflow 是一个看门人。

We set the start_date to 9 am today and the interval to “@hourly”. It means that we have told Airflow to start working at 9 am and move some boxes at the beginning of every hour.我们将 start_date 设置为今天上午 9 点，并将间隔设置为“@hourly”。这意味着我们已经告诉 Airflow 在上午 9 点开始工作，并在每小时开始时搬运一些箱子。

Our janitor comes to work at 9 am as expected. Do you think that he/she starts working right away? Obviously no. First, the coffee has to be made. After that, there is a time for watching or reading the news. No work is done between 9 am and 10 am.我们的清洁工如期早上 9 点来上班。您认为他/她会立即开始工作吗？显然不是。首先，必须煮咖啡。之后，就有时间看或读新闻。上午 9 点到 10 点之间不进行任何工作。

What happens at 10 am? The “hourly” interval has passed, and now it is time to move some data around. The same happens at 11 am and later — every hour. At this, point my example breaks down because the real janitor goes home at 5 pm, but Airflow is going to continue working at repeat the same job every hour. Continuously, even at night.上午 10 点会发生什么？ “每小时”间隔已经过去，现在是时候移动一些数据了。同样的情况发生在上午 11 点及之后的时间——每小时一次。此时，我的示例就失效了，因为真正的清洁工在下午 5 点回家，但 Airflow 将继续每小时重复相同的工作。持续不断，甚至在晚上。

Start date开始日期

The problem is that “start_date” parameter is counterintuitive. The job does not start at this time. So what starts?问题是“start_date”参数是违反直觉的。此时作业尚未开始。那么什么开始呢？

In Airflow start_date is the time when Airflow starts the timer. It just starts measuring the time.在 Airflow 中，start_date 是 Airflow 启动计时器的时间。它刚刚开始测量时间。

How to write to a Parquet file in Scala without using Apache Spark如何在不使用 Apache Spark 的情况下在 Scala 中写入 Parquet 文件

How to use Parquet4s to write Parquet files in Scala如何在Scala中使用Parquet4s编写Parquet文件
Bartosz Mikulski 10 May 2019 – 2 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2019 年 5 月 10 日 – 阅读 2 分钟

What to do when you want to store something in a Parquet file when writing a standard Scala application, not an Apache Spark job? You can use the project created by my colleague — Parquet4S.当您在编写标准 Scala 应用程序而不是 Apache Spark 作业时想要将某些内容存储在 Parquet 文件中时该怎么办？你可以使用我同事 创建的项目—— Parquet4S。

First, I am going to create a custom class with custom type parameters (I also included all of the imports in the first code snippet).首先，我将创建一个具有自定义类型参数的自定义类（我还在第一个代码片段中包含了所有导入）。

import akka.actor.ActorSystem
import akka.stream.ActorMaterializer
import akka.stream.scaladsl.Source
import org.apache.parquet.hadoop.ParquetFileWriter
import org.apache.parquet.hadoop.metadata.CompressionCodecName
import com.github.mjakubowski84.parquet4s._
import org.apache.parquet.schema.{OriginalType, PrimitiveType}
import com.github.mjakubowski84.parquet4s.ParquetSchemaResolver._

import scala.concurrent.duration._
import scala.concurrent.Await

case class Email(value: String) extends AnyVal
case class FirstName(value: String) extends AnyVal
case class LastName(value: String) extends AnyVal

case class User(firstName: FirstName, lastName: LastName, email: Email)

Because I don’t use Scala built-in types, I have to define the codecs and schemas of those custom types.因为我不使用 Scala 内置类型，所以我必须定义这些自定义类型的编解码器和架构。

implicit val firstNameTypeCodec: OptionalValueCodec[FirstName] =
  new OptionalValueCodec[FirstName] {
    override protected def decodeNonNull(value: Value, configuration: ValueCodecConfiguration): FirstName = value match {
      case StringValue(string) => FirstName(string)
    }
    override protected def encodeNonNull(data: FirstName, configuration: ValueCodecConfiguration): Value =
      StringValue(data.value)
  }

implicit val firstNameSchema: TypedSchemaDef[FirstName] =
  typedSchemaDef[FirstName](
    PrimitiveSchemaDef(
      primitiveType = PrimitiveType.PrimitiveTypeName.BINARY,
      required = true,
      originalType = Some(OriginalType.UTF8)
    )
  )

implicit val lastNameTypeCodec: OptionalValueCodec[LastName] =
  new OptionalValueCodec[LastName] {
    override protected def decodeNonNull(value: Value, configuration: ValueCodecConfiguration): LastName = value match {
      case StringValue(string) => LastName(string)
    }
    override protected def encodeNonNull(data: LastName, configuration: ValueCodecConfiguration): Value =
      StringValue(data.value)
  }

implicit val lastNameSchema: TypedSchemaDef[LastName] =
  typedSchemaDef[LastName](
    PrimitiveSchemaDef(
      primitiveType = PrimitiveType.PrimitiveTypeName.BINARY,
      required = true,
      originalType = Some(OriginalType.UTF8)
    )
  )

implicit val emailTypeCodec: OptionalValueCodec[Email] =
  new OptionalValueCodec[Email] {
    override protected def decodeNonNull(value: Value, configuration: ValueCodecConfiguration): Email = value match {
      case StringValue(string) => Email(string)
    }
    override protected def encodeNonNull(data: Email, configuration: ValueCodecConfiguration): Value =
      StringValue(data.value)
  }

implicit val emailSchema: TypedSchemaDef[Email] =
  typedSchemaDef[Email](
    PrimitiveSchemaDef(
      primitiveType = PrimitiveType.PrimitiveTypeName.BINARY,
      required = true,
      originalType = Some(OriginalType.UTF8)
    )
  )

Calculating the cumulative sum of a group using Apache Spark使用 Apache Spark 计算组的累积和

How to use the window function to calculate a cumulative sum如何使用窗口函数计算累积和
Bartosz Mikulski 20 May 2019 – 1 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2019 年 5 月 20 日 – 阅读 1 分钟

A cumulative sum (or a running total) is a sequence of partial sums of a given sorted dataset. In this article, I will explain how to use Apache Spark to calculate the cumulative sum of values grouped by a column.累积和（或运行总计）是给定排序数据集的部分和的序列。在本文中，我将解释如何使用 Apache Spark 计算按列分组的值的累积和。

Imagine that I have loaded a data Spark dataset, which contains credit card transactions. The dataset consists of two columns: date (a date column) and amount (float type). I want to group the payments by year and month and calculate the total amount spent during that month.想象一下，我已经加载了一个 Spark 数据集，其中包含信用卡交易。数据集由两列组成：日期（日期列）和金额（浮点类型）。我想按年份和月份对付款进行分组，并计算该月的支出总额。

To create a single grouping column, I concatenate the year to the month:为了创建单个分组列，我将年份连接到月份：

val withMonth = data.withColumn("yearWithMonth", concat(year($"date"), month($"date")))

Now, it is time to define the window used to calculate the cumulative sum. I use the newly created column as my partitioning key:现在，是时候定义用于计算累积和的窗口了。我使用新创建的列作为分区键：

val window = Window
  .partitionBy($"yearWithMonth")

As the second parameter, I specify the order, because I want the payments to be sorted:作为第二个参数，我指定顺序，因为我希望对付款进行排序：

val window = Window
  .partitionBy($"yearWithMonth")
  .orderBy($"date".asc)

Finally, I use the rowsBetween function to specify the window range (note that you should NOT use the rangeBetween function, because it works on the actual values of the rows, not their position. In this case we want to group by position within the partition).最后，我使用 rowsBetween 函数来指定窗口范围（请注意，您不应该使用 rangeBetween 函数，因为它适用于行的实际值，而不是行的位置。在这种情况下，我们希望按分区内的位置进行分组）。

It crates a window that contains values between the first row of the dataset (sorted) and the currently processed row:它创建一个窗口，其中包含数据集第一行（已排序）和当前处理行之间的值：

val window = Window
  .partitionBy($"yearWithMonth")
  .orderBy($"date".asc)
  .rowsBetween(Window.unboundedPreceding, Window.currentRow)

Now, I can use the sum function with the window to get the cumulative sum:现在，我可以将 sum 函数与窗口一起使用来获取累积和：

withMonth.withColumn("spentPerMonth", sum($"spent").over(window))

A quick warning. It turned out that I did not want to know the total value of my credit card transactions since the day I opened the bank account. Make sure that you want to see it before you use your credit card data ;)快速警告。事实证明，我不想知道自开设银行账户之日起我的信用卡交易总价值。确保您想在使用信用卡数据之前查看它；）

Row number in Apache Spark window — row_number, rank, and dense_rankApache Spark 窗口中的行号 — row_number、rank 和 dendense_rank

This article is mostly a “note to self” because I don’t want to google that anymore ;)这篇文章主要是“自我注释”，因为我不想再用谷歌搜索它了;)
Bartosz Mikulski 08 May 2019 – 1 min read 巴托斯·米库尔斯基 2019 年 5 月 8 日 – 阅读 1 分钟

This article is mostly a “note to self” because I don’t want to google that anymore ;)这篇文章主要是“自我注释”，因为我不想再用谷歌搜索它了;)

Which function should we use to rank the rows within a window in Apache Spark data frame?我们应该使用哪个函数对 Apache Spark 数据框中窗口内的行进行排名？

It depends on the expected output. row_number is going to sort the output by the column specified in orderBy function and return the index of the row (human-readable, so starts from 1).这取决于预期的输出。 row_number 将按 orderBy 函数中指定的列对输出进行排序，并返回行的索引（人类可读，因此从 1 开始）。

The only difference between rank and dense_rank is the fact that the rank function is going to skip the numbers if there are duplicates assigned to the same rank. In the same situation, the dense_rank function uses the next number in a sequence.等级和密集等级之间的唯一区别是，如果有重复分配给同一等级，则等级函数将跳过数字。在相同的情况下，dense_rank 函数使用序列中的下一个数字。

I found this great example on StackOverflow that seems to explain everything:我在 StackOverflow 上发现了这个很好的例子，它似乎解释了一切：

import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._

val df = Seq(("a", 10), ("a", 10), ("a", 20)).toDF("col1", "col2")

val windowSpec = Window.partitionBy("col1").orderBy("col2")

df
  .withColumn("rank", rank().over(windowSpec))
  .withColumn("dense_rank", dense_rank().over(windowSpec))
  .withColumn("row_number", row_number().over(windowSpec)).show

+----+----+----+----------+----------+
|col1|col2|rank|dense_rank|row_number|
+----+----+----+----------+----------+
|   a|  10|   1|         1|         1|
|   a|  10|   1|         1|         2|
|   a|  20|   3|         2|         3|
+----+----+----+----------+----------+

Source: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44968912/difference-in-dense-rank-and-row-number-in-spark资料来源：https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44968912/difference-in-dense-rank-and-row-number-in-spark
